message.content:
My mistress' eyes are nothing like the sun;  
Coral is far more red than her lips' red;  
If snow be white, why then her breasts are dun;  
Her hair's a frizzy mess upon her head.  

I've seen some roses in a fancy shop,  
But her cheeks look like pizza, greasy-cheese;  
She walks with such an awkward, clumsy hop,  
And sniffles loudly when she has a sneeze.  

Her perfume smells like old gym socks, not flowers,  
She binge-watches Netflix every night;  
My love for her defies all logic's powers—  
Her TikTok dances give me second-hand fright.  

But hey, she's got a really cool smartphone,  
So I guess she'll do, since I'm alone.
